Dallas Investor ‘Shad’ Rowe Named to Texas Pension Fund Board by Speaker

-- B y   D a v i d   M i l d e n b e r g
-- 
2011-12-01T23:41:37Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-12-01/dallas-investor-shad-rowe-named-to-texas-pension-fund-board-by-speaker.html
Frederick “Shad” Rowe Jr., a  Dallas 
investor who has voiced alarm over underfunded public pensions,
was named to the board overseeing the state’s $23.6 billion
Employees Retirement System.  Joe Straus, the Republican speaker of the  House of
Representatives , appointed Rowe to complete an unexpired term
that ends in August 2014, subject to Senate confirmation,
according to a statement from Straus’s office. Rowe is chairman
of Greenbrier Partners Fund in Dallas and a former head of the
Texas Pension Review Board.  To contact the reporter on this story:
David Mildenberg in Austin, Texas, at 
 dmildenberg@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Mark Tannenbaum at 
 mtannen@bloomberg.net  